definitions.definition: Every individual or anything of the given class, with no exceptions (the noun or noun phrase denoting the class must be plural or uncountable).
examples: All contestants must register for the footrace: we've arranged numbers for them all .
All (the) three of my nephews adore classical music.

definitions.definition: Throughout the whole of (a stated period of time; generally used with units of a day or longer).
examples: The store is open all day and all night.
I’ve been working on this all year.
He's all talk; he never puts his ideas into practice.
